00:30:42,598 --> 00:30:47,241
that now are much more inclusive and anybody can turn up.

546
00:30:47,301 --> 00:30:53,464
And I think that helps with the funnel of trying to get more voices in there.

547
00:30:53,524 --> 00:30:59,147
Like, if you're not even able to go to a convention space and feel comfortable playing those games,

548
00:30:59,167 --> 00:31:02,669
then you're probably not going to try to design board games at all.

549
00:31:02,789 --> 00:31:05,111
So I think that's part of the step.

550
00:31:06,889 --> 00:31:15,095
I mean, I think we've discussed that financial stability is very important and there is a cultural element to financial stability.

551
00:31:15,135 --> 00:31:22,581
There are more, you know, wealth gaps, pay gaps, all of these things are true depending on, you know, kind of.

552
00:31:23,287 --> 00:31:25,428
where you exist and that will affect whether or not you can

553
00:31:26,329 --> 00:31:28,830
succeed or you feel comfortable attempting to succeed in the industry.

