00:35:34,169 --> 00:35:36,190
And he had a friend in Germany, Jeffrey Allers,

617
00:35:36,250 --> 00:35:37,671
who said, will you please bring it to Germany?

618
00:35:37,691 --> 00:35:38,772
I want to try it and play it.

619
00:35:39,792 --> 00:35:41,733
We're going to meet up at this board game cafe,

620
00:35:41,753 --> 00:35:44,895
Spiel Weiss, which I think was one of the very first board game cafes.

621
00:35:45,355 --> 00:35:46,336
and I'd really like to play it there.

622
00:35:46,396 --> 00:35:49,196
So Eric brought Quirkle to Germany

623
00:35:49,236 --> 00:35:51,036
and played it with Jeffrey and Michael,

624
00:35:51,056 --> 00:35:53,337
who owns the cafe, and Torsten Gimler,

625
00:35:53,817 --> 00:35:55,197
who is the publisher at Schmichtbill,

626
00:35:55,217 --> 00:35:57,618
and Torsten is the person who ended up licensing Quirkle

627
00:35:57,678 --> 00:35:59,278
for the German publisher.

