00:36:25,330 --> 00:36:27,732
I think if we hadn't been reaching out

638
00:36:27,832 --> 00:36:31,716
to different content reviewers sort of people,

639
00:36:32,756 --> 00:36:33,937
Quirkle might not have had that.

640
00:36:36,264 --> 00:36:38,365
might not have found a home among gamers that it did.

641
00:36:38,385 --> 00:36:39,986
It would have just stayed in the family game market

642
00:36:40,006 --> 00:36:41,066
and it spread from there.

643
00:36:41,146 --> 00:36:45,869
So very personal experience of value of board game cafes.

644
00:36:46,869 --> 00:36:47,829
And then the other thing is,

645
00:36:49,430 --> 00:36:51,571
one of the things that I think is super exciting

646
00:36:51,611 --> 00:36:54,733
about games right now is the growing base of gamers

647
00:36:54,813 --> 00:36:57,474
are people who are excited about learning new games.

648
00:36:57,554 --> 00:36:59,175
And I think American gamers for.

649
00:37:01,047 --> 00:37:06,014
a long, long time, I don't know how long, have been afraid of learning games. Families

650
00:37:06,094 --> 00:37:11,161
have played the games that they grew up, you know, parents played Payday or Monopoly or

651
00:37:11,241 --> 00:37:14,846
Scrabble or Parcheesi or Sorry. They played those games growing up.

652
00:37:15,294 --> 00:37:17,396
And when they have kids, they buy the same games

653
00:37:17,476 --> 00:37:18,877
because they don't want to learn new games.

654
00:37:19,897 --> 00:37:23,099
And it's been a huge barrier of entry for American gamers

655
00:37:23,179 --> 00:37:24,200
to learn new games.

656
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:27,222
And right now, I think in part because of board game cafes

657
00:37:27,262 --> 00:37:30,464
and in part because of all the videos teaching games,

658
00:37:31,185 --> 00:37:33,686
we're experiencing this spread of people

659
00:37:33,767 --> 00:37:36,688
who like to learn new games, which is totally different

660
00:37:36,729 --> 00:37:37,729
than what we've had before.

661
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:41,131
And I think there is going to be a driving force,

662
00:37:41,212 --> 00:37:43,193
even though I think we're headed towards a problem

663
00:37:43,213 --> 00:37:44,594
with oversaturation of games.

664
00:37:45,054 --> 00:37:49,738
I think creating people who think learning games is fun is going to change our market

665
00:37:49,798 --> 00:37:50,298
entirely.

666
00:37:51,219 --> 00:37:55,302
People who think that it's fun to try something new and introduce their friends to it and

667
00:37:55,322 --> 00:37:58,144
they're going to do it at board game cafes and they're going to do it by watching videos

668
00:37:58,164 --> 00:37:59,165
and learning games that way.

669
00:37:59,725 --> 00:38:03,168
I think that's a really strong force in our market right now.

670
00:38:03,593 --> 00:38:07,638
I think that's a really interesting point. Do we think that digital content creators

671
00:38:08,238 --> 00:38:12,563
are part of the reason that the hobbies exploded so much? Because there's now so much learn

672
00:38:12,583 --> 00:38:18,409
to play stuff. There's so much in terms of board game reviews on the internet. And when

673
00:38:18,449 --> 00:38:21,752
people speak to me about discovering a board game, they often say, I didn't see it in a

674
00:38:21,792 --> 00:38:26,457
shop. I definitely didn't see an ad for it anywhere. I watched a review of it or something

675
00:38:26,497 --> 00:38:27,298
like that on YouTube.

676
00:38:28,676 --> 00:38:33,458
I think definitely similarly on Kickstarter people are also courting content creators

677
00:38:33,558 --> 00:38:36,500
to like get the word out about their games and I think part of that is just

678
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:42,743
because the internet is, it is the most powerful like marketing tool anyone can have

679
00:38:43,403 --> 00:38:46,645
and YouTube is huge, right, Twitter is enormous and those,

680
00:38:47,585 --> 00:38:51,027
like as those tools get more powerful, like everyone wants to use those

681
00:38:51,067 --> 00:38:53,989
to market whatever their product is whether it's board games or anything else

682
00:38:54,029 --> 00:38:55,810
and so we are seeing a benefit from that.

683
00:38:57,603 --> 00:39:02,187
There are even some concerns about like, you know, oh, if I want to learn to play this game, I'm not going to go to my local board game shop.

